// EXPECTED: compile error
//
// Regression: `async fn()` called as a regular call (not via the
// state-machine init/poll pair). Pre-fix, the checker accepted this;
// the emitter renamed the function to `_zer_async_NAME_init/poll`,
// leaving the bare call as a dangling symbol — GCC implicit-declaration
// warning + linker undefined-reference (confusing two-stage failure).
//
// Fix: checker recognizes Symbol.is_async at NODE_CALL and rejects
// with a helpful diagnostic pointing at the proper init/poll dispatch.
async void worker() {
    yield;
}

void main() {
    worker();  // ← must be rejected: "cannot call async function as a regular call"
}
